  "prompt": "What should I do if my PayPal account is hacked?",
  "response": "If your PayPal account is hacked, it's important to act quickly to minimize any potential damage. Here are the steps you should take:\n\n1. **Change Your Password**: Immediately change your PayPal password to something strong and unique. Avoid using common words and include numbers, special characters, and a mix of uppercase and lowercase letters.\n\n2. **Enable Two-Factor Authentication (2FA)**: If you haven't already, enable 2FA on your PayPal account. This adds an extra layer of security by requiring a second form of identification, such as a code sent to your phone.\n\n3. **Check Recent Activity**: Review your account for any unauthorized transactions or changes to your personal information. Make a note of any suspicious activity.\n\n4. **Report Unauthorized Transactions**: If you find any transactions you did not authorize, report them to PayPal immediately. You can do this through the Resolution Center on the PayPal website.\n\n5. **Contact PayPal Support**: Reach out to PayPal's customer service for further assistance. You can contact them via phone, email, or through the help section on their site.\n\n6. **Update Security Settings**: Review and update your security questions and other account settings to ensure they haven\u2019t been altered by the hacker.\n\n7. **Check Linked Accounts**: If your PayPal account is linked to other financial accounts or services, double-check those accounts for any unusual activity. Consider changing passwords for those accounts as well.\n\n8. **Run a Security Scan**: Run a security scan on your devices to check for malware or viruses that might have contributed to the hack. Use trusted antivirus software.\n\n9. **Monitor Your Account**: Keep a close eye on your PayPal account and other financial accounts for the next few weeks to ensure no further unauthorized activity occurs.\n\n10. **Inform Your Bank**: Notify your bank if you believe that the hacker may have obtained your banking information. They can help you take additional protective measures.\n\nRemember to stay vigilant and regularly update your passwords and security settings to avoid future incidents.",
